The Fix: Refresh your Mirrorlist
Since you're ricing, you need a mirrorlist that actually works for your location. You can fix this manually once, or add these lines to the top of your script to make it "location-aware."

1. Install Reflector (The Gold Standard)
Reflector is a tool that fetches the latest mirror list from the Arch Linux website, filters them by speed/status, and overwrites your /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist.

Bash
# Force an update of the local DB so we can at least get reflector
sudo pacman -Sy --noconfirm --needed reflector
